## Issue 2 — Tapping an Article Card → 404

**Investigate first:**

The Tab 4 → generic `/blog` route was already fixed (registered in root `_layout.tsx`).
This 404 is happening when navigating to a **specific article** with a slug/URL param,
which is a different navigation call than the generic one. Most likely cause: the
specific-article navigation passes params in a way that either:
- Targets a route that was never registered (e.g. if article taps try to push to
  `/blog/[slug]` as a separate route instead of reusing `/blog` with an `initialUrl`
  param, per the original spec in `TASK_MOBILE_BLOG_ACCESS.md` Phase 3.2), or
- Passes the param correctly to `/blog`, but the WebView screen component doesn't
  actually read/use `initialUrl` from `useLocalSearchParams()` (or whatever the
  Mobile project's param-reading convention is) and always falls back to the generic
  blog index — which wouldn't 404, so check this only if the first explanation doesn't
  match what's observed.

```bash
grep -n "router.push" Mobile/app/\(tabs\)/home/index.tsx | grep -i blog
grep -n "useLocalSearchParams\|initialUrl" Mobile/app/blog/index.tsx
```

**Fix:** ensure article taps navigate to the registered `/blog` route (not a
non-existent nested route), passing the specific article URL as a param:
```tsx
router.push({ pathname: '/blog', params: { initialUrl: `https://ketocakelab.com/blog/${post.slug}` } });
```
And confirm `Mobile/app/blog/index.tsx` reads this param and uses it as the WebView's
`source.uri`, defaulting to the generic blog index when absent — exactly as specified
in the original task. If this logic was never implemented (only the generic `/blog`
case was), implement it now.

